At the same time, he said he was confident in the proper resolution of the maritime boundary dispute between Peru and Chile in the same court and that it is “beneficial for Latin America to refer the matter to international bodies if the two countries agree to accept a judgment as firm as it may be”.
In reference to the possibility of his nomination as a candidate in the future presidential elections in Ecuador, with a view to running for a third consecutive term, he pointed out that he saw this possibility "with great optimism and joy, although it is sometimes quite difficult".
